from Kansas City?

14:41.700 --> 14:43.233
No. Libby's with me.

14:43.269 --> 14:44.501
I'm sorry?

14:44.536 --> 14:47.671
[Libby] I came with Virginia.

14:47.706 --> 14:48.939
[Johnson] Is that a problem?

14:48.974 --> 14:52.142
Art encouraged me to bring a friend.

14:52.177 --> 14:55.345
No, it's not a problem at
all. Let's get you two some drinks.

14:55.381 --> 14:56.847
We've hired this wonderful bartender

14:56.882 --> 14:58.815
who does amazing things with tequila.

14:58.851 --> 15:01.785
Michael, I thought this
lovely woman was your girlfriend.

15:01.820 --> 15:04.021
Lisa? No. We split up.

15:04.056 --> 15:06.590
She kept insisting she
was my rebound after Erica.

15:06.625 --> 15:08.659
Uh, my wife. Well, ex-wife.

15:08.694 --> 15:09.927
So you're here alone?

15:09.962 --> 15:11.995
I am so sorry about that,

15:12.031 --> 15:14.131
but it does really
help with our numbers.

15:14.166 --> 15:16.333
Michael Schaeffer, this is Virginia...

15:16.368 --> 15:19.636
Now do you go by Johnson or
Logan outside the office?

15:19.672 --> 15:21.705
How old-fashioned is
that husband of yours?

15:21.740 --> 15:23.807
Dan's fine with either, so
I've stuck with Johnson.

15:23.842 --> 15:26.643
Dan Logan is your husband?

15:26.679 --> 15:28.612
[laughing]

15:28.647 --> 15:30.547
I'll be damned. Uh, the three of us

15:30.582 --> 15:32.661
are supposed to be having dinner
next week in New York.

15:32.685 --> 15:34.217
We are?

15:34.253 --> 15:36.620
Mike. Mike
Schaeffer. He didn't mention it?

15:36.655 --> 15:39.222
No... of course. Mike.

15:39.258 --> 15:40.490
Mike Schaeffer. Yes.

15:40.526 --> 15:41.858
Hey, I suggested a restaurant,

15:41.894 --> 15:43.338
but he said you were a fabulous cook.

15:43.362 --> 15:44.528
He said Virginia was?

15:44.563 --> 15:47.397
I make one or two things well.

15:47.433 --> 15:50.000
That reminds me, I have
completely forgotten

15:50.035 --> 15:52.135
to leave dinner
instructions with the babysitter.

15:52.171 --> 15:54.304
If you'll excuse me,
may I use your phone?

15:54.340 --> 15:56.306
In the kitchen... I'll show you.

15:56.342 --> 15:58.709
[Nancy] Harry... and
Linda, don't you look pretty!

15:58.744 --> 16:00.210
Coats in the bedroom, everyone.

16:00.245 --> 16:02.079
Hi. Libby Masters.

16:02.114 --> 16:03.880
I'm also divorced.

16:03.916 --> 16:05.716
Does seem to be going around these days.

16:08.921 --> 16:12.022
John? Jenny?

16:12.057 --> 16:13.323
Howie? Come on, shake a leg.

16:13.359 --> 16:15.025
[puppy yipping and growling]

16:15.060 --> 16:18.061
[puppy whining]

16:20.733 --> 16:22.432
Howie?

16:22.468 --> 16:24.067
Jenny?

16:26.739 --> 16:28.905
Kids?

16:28.941 --> 16:30.240
[puppy barks]

16:35.481 --> 16:36.446
You having fun?

16:36.482 --> 16:38.248
Betty met Mookie.

16:38.283 --> 16:41.918
Yeah. Very big with the hand
gestures, that Mookie.

16:41.954 --> 16:43.887
- Do we have any seltzer?
- Guess what, honey.

16:43.922 --> 16:47.257
Turns out Mike Schaeffer knows
Virginia's husband, Dan.

16:47.292 --> 16:48.803
- [Art] Is that right?
- [Nancy] They're all getting

16:48.827 --> 16:50.527
together in New York in a few weeks.

16:50.562 --> 16:52.596
You know, we'd love to meet Dan,

16:52.631 --> 16:54.109
maybe the next time he's in St. Louis.

16:54.133 --> 16:55.732
Great.

16:55.768 --> 16:58.201
Hey, Nance, uh, I could
use your help for a sec.

16:58.237 --> 16:59.903
Will you excuse me a moment?

17:01.573 --> 17:03.940
You know what works even
better than seltzer, Art,

17:03.976 --> 17:05.809
is ginger ale.

17:05.844 --> 17:08.111
Give me one sec.

17:08.146 --> 17:10.781
Ginger ale does not get out stains.

17:10.816 --> 17:12.616
I know that.

17:15.988 --> 17:17.554
What?

17:17.589 --> 17:19.823
Really? You want me to say it?

17:19.858 --> 17:21.590
[gentle piano music playing]

17:21.627 --> 17:24.560
What are you gonna do when this
Mike guy gets back from New York

17:24.596 --> 17:25.962
and says to these two,

17:25.998 --> 17:27.731
"Hey, guess who isn't
married to Dan Logan."

17:27.766 --> 17:29.566
Shh, shh, shh.

17:29.601 --> 17:31.479
She thinks I don't know where
they're coming from.

17:31.503 --> 17:32.769
Oh.

17:32.805 --> 17:34.171
Like a person could actually just,

17:34.206 --> 17:35.972
in the course of their normal life,

17:36.008 --> 17:40.310
bump into that many
people who make balloon animals.

17:40.345 --> 17:41.745
You know what the ironic thing is?

17:41.780 --> 17:43.080
Do you?

17:43.115 --> 17:44.981
Well, do you?

17:45.017 --> 17:46.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:46.385 --> 17:47.751
What is the ironic thing?

17:47.786 --> 17:49.486
I got the tickets

17:49.521 --> 17:52.622
for her and little Hugo to
see the stupid fucking show.

17:52.658 --> 17:55.092
- Are you gonna finish that?
- I was...

17:55.160 --> 17:56.660
[Lester] I'll grab us a couple more.

17:56.695 --> 17:59.129
You don't think that
six months is too soon

17:59.164 --> 18:01.031
to get seriously
involved with someone new?

18:01.066 --> 18:03.166
Ah, you sound like Lisa. Look, I swear

18:03.202 --> 18:05.035
I wasn't rebounding, all right?

18:05.070 --> 18:07.838
I mean, she was just
threatened by how close Erica and I are.

18:07.873 --> 18:10.273
- You mind?
- Oh, no.

18:10.309 --> 18:13.710
[indistinct chatter, polite applause]

18:13.745 --> 18:16.546
We actually renewed our vows.

18:16.582 --> 18:18.348
You and your ex?

18:18.383 --> 18:20.717
Yep. It was Erica's therapist's idea

18:20.752 --> 18:21.985
to do it for Nicky and Aaron.

18:22.020 --> 18:23.320
- Uh-huh.
- We solemnly pledged

18:23.355 --> 18:25.322
to love each other, not
as husband and wife,

18:25.357 --> 18:28.558
but as best friends.

18:28.594 --> 18:31.628
You actually had a ceremony?

18:31.663 --> 18:34.030
That is so beautiful.

18:34.066 --> 18:35.398
And how about you?

18:35.434 --> 18:38.168
How about you and your ex?

18:38.203 --> 18:39.402
Are you close?

18:39.438 --> 18:43.707
Uh, uh... very close.

18:43.742 --> 18:45.609
Yeah, extremely close.

18:48.714 --> 18:51.081
Bill and I have found, um...

18:54.553 --> 18:56.419
Um, his name is Bill.

18:56.455 --> 19:00.090
But as long as we can sit down
and take each other by the hand

19:00.125 --> 19:01.825
and really just say, you know,

19:01.860 --> 19:06.830
"Honey, you know how much I
love you and I value you,"

19:06.865 --> 19:08.498
um, then everything
that comes after that

19:08.534 --> 19:10.367
just goes so much more easily.

19:10.402 --> 19:13.103
Yeah, there's no moving on until
you're good with your ex.

19:13.138 --> 19:14.771
- [man] Come on in.
- Mm.

19:14.806 --> 19:17.841
[indistinct chatter]

19:17.876 --> 19:19.509
Um, Mike, do you mind...

19:19.545 --> 19:21.244
Just switch places with
you really quick?

19:21.280 --> 19:23.046
Libby Masters?

19:25.317 --> 19:28.251
Boy... girl...

19:30.155 --> 19:31.421
Boy? Girl? I can't tell.

19:31.456 --> 19:32.956
Boy's or girl's?

19:32.991 --> 19:35.192
Mm. Oh, that's, uh, Debbie DeLaurio's.

19:35.227 --> 19:37.694
She and Glenn just got
back from a cruise in Acapulco.

19:37.729 --> 19:39.529
They say buffet adds a pound a day.

19:39.565 --> 19:42.599
I'd say they were
gone about a month. You?

19:42.634 --> 19:44.968
Easy. Art happens to like a woman

19:45.003 --> 19:46.303
with a little meat on her bones.

19:46.338 --> 19:47.804
You know what I like.

19:47.839 --> 19:49.306
What do you like?

19:49.341 --> 19:51.741
I like you.

19:51.777 --> 19:54.945
You know, sooner or later,
just statistically speaking,

19:54.980 --> 19:57.814
it's gonna be, you know, us.

19:57.849 --> 19:59.282
You and me.

20:05.857 --> 20:07.591
Got it?

20:07.626 --> 20:08.959
The fix is in.

20:11.330 --> 20:12.963
Two olives.

20:12.998 --> 20:14.598
[indistinct chatter]

20:14.633 --> 20:17.968
Coats, huh? Well, I dig it.

20:18.003 --> 20:19.736
[chuckles] Well, well, well.

20:19.771 --> 20:22.839
I have to say you're the
last person I expected to find

20:22.874 --> 20:23.907
at a party like this.

20:23.942 --> 20:26.276
Party like what?

20:26.311 --> 20:30.080
Oh, well, I occasionally imbibe.

20:30.115 --> 20:31.781
You know, as shrewd a judge of character

20:31.817 --> 20:33.316
as I consider myself to be,

20:33.352 --> 20:36.786
I have to admit I have
seriously misjudged you,

20:36.822 --> 20:38.521
Libby Masters.

20:38.557 --> 20:40.368
- Bram Keller. How do you do?
- Yeah. Nice to meet you.

20:40.392 --> 20:42.170
Definitely more to this
lady than meets the eye.

20:42.194 --> 20:43.960
- Mike.
- You'd think prim and proper,

20:43.996 --> 20:46.196
wouldn't you, Ike, just
based on outward appearances?

20:46.231 --> 20:48.465
But I am telling you, this one, inside,

20:48.500 --> 20:50.800
is a roiling cauldron of rage.

20:50.836 --> 20:53.336
You just tap her ever
so slightly, and...

20:53.372 --> 20:54.771
[imitates explosion] Mount Etna.

20:54.806 --> 20:57.874
That is not true. That's not true.

20:57.909 --> 21:01.177
Mr. Keller and I recently
had a very unpleasant dealing.

21:01.213 --> 21:03.013
I'm representing her ex in a lawsuit,

21:03.048 --> 21:05.982
and this one would rather see
him strung up by his ball sack

21:06.018 --> 21:07.384
than lift a finger to help.

21:07.419 --> 21:08.718
I... that's not at all...

21:08.754 --> 21:10.887
Hey, no apologies
necessary. I, for one, find

21:10.922 --> 21:13.623
a beautiful woman with a
filthy mouth extremely appealing.

21:13.659 --> 21:15.325
Are you and Mark here an item?

21:15.360 --> 21:16.871
- Uh, no, we're not.
- We just met each other.

21:16.895 --> 21:18.962
In fact, I'm gonna...
I'm gonna get a refill.

21:18.997 --> 21:20.742
- Oh, great. Great idea.
- Would you bring me another...

21:20.766 --> 21:23.700
Hey, pal, if you want to do a
little do-si-do with Gloria,

21:23.735 --> 21:25.335
the gal I walked in here with,

21:25.370 --> 21:27.737
she's got quite a beaver.

21:27.773 --> 21:29.739
What?

21:29.775 --> 21:31.141
Her coat is beaver.

21:31.176 --> 21:34.311
Care to tell me what yours looks like?

21:34.346 --> 21:36.079
My coat...

21:36.114 --> 21:38.315
is a plaid cape.

21:38.350 --> 21:40.150
Why on earth would
you want to know that?

21:40.185 --> 21:43.553
Do you really not know what
kind of party this is?

21:43.588 --> 21:45.208
[lively piano music playing]

21:45.459 --> 21:46.936
I'm going to clear
all this up about Dan.

21:46.960 --> 21:48.927
I am. Soon.

21:48.962 --> 21:50.495
Soon is too far away.

21:50.530 --> 21:52.163
[sighs]

21:52.199 --> 21:54.599
Virginia, there's no
shame in it not working out.

21:54.635 --> 21:57.636
In fact, there's a certain kind of honor

21:57.671 --> 21:59.437
in recognizing right at the beginning

21:59.473 --> 22:01.673
that a marriage is not meant to be

22:01.708 --> 22:02.774
and ending it.

22:02.809 --> 22:04.342
Dan and I didn't get married.

22:04.378 --> 22:06.711
It never got that far.

22:10.851 --> 22:13.818
Well, you at least got to tell Bill.

22:13.854 --> 22:15.353
He's gonna find out, Virginia.

22:15.389 --> 22:17.822
It's better if he finds out from you.

22:17.858 --> 22:19.457
For the life of me, I can't figure out

22:19.493 --> 22:20.959
why Helen would rather risk

22:20.994 --> 22:22.861
her parents finding
out about me by accident

22:22.896 --> 22:24.429
than just sitting them down

22:24.464 --> 22:25.931
and telling them the truth.

22:25.966 --> 22:28.300
- [doorbell rings]
- I'll tell him. I will.

22:28.335 --> 22:29.701
Tomorrow.

22:29.736 --> 22:31.214
[door clicks, man speaking indistinctly]

22:31.238 --> 22:32.804
No time like the present.

22:32.839 --> 22:37.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:37.844 --> 22:40.612
- Hiya, Bill.
- [Bill] Where are the kids?

22:40.647 --> 22:43.548
Um, Jenny's at her
friend Rebecca's house,

22:43.799 --> 22:46.367
and Howie and Johnny are
at Tommy Hershfeld's.

22:46.402 --> 22:48.113
- Excuse me.
- Well, they were supposed to be

22:48.137 --> 22:50.015
with me tonight, you
knew I'd made plans with them.

22:50.039 --> 22:51.350
- You didn't think to call?
- [stammers]

22:51.374 --> 22:53.007
It must have slipped my mind, Bill.

22:53.042 --> 22:54.887
Excuse me. Is there a
black and white cape back there?

22:54.911 --> 22:56.511
So you made me go all
the way over there?

22:56.546 --> 22:59.246
I'm sorry, Bill. Did I selfishly
inconvenience you?

22:59.282 --> 23:01.515
Did I thoughtlessly capitulate
to the children

23:01.551 --> 23:04.051
without any concern for
how it affected you?

23:05.321 --> 23:06.954
- Where you going?
- Home.

23:08.658 --> 23:09.890
[glass clinking]

23:09.926 --> 23:11.959
- [man] Ooh.
- [man] Oh, here we go.

23:11.994 --> 23:13.294
Okay!

23:13.329 --> 23:16.263
Okay, everybody. Settle
down, boys and girls.

23:16.299 --> 23:17.531
[Nancy chuckles]

23:17.567 --> 23:19.400
Now, before we get started,

23:19.435 --> 23:21.936
we have a few newcomers tonight.

23:21.971 --> 23:25.773
- [woman] Ooh, la-la.
- So let's review the procedure.

23:25.808 --> 23:27.575
- Art?
- Okay, well,

23:27.610 --> 23:29.109
tonight it's gentlemen's choice.

23:29.145 --> 23:30.744
- All right!
- Whoo!

23:30.780 --> 23:33.113
[Art] No do-overs unless you
get the person you came with.

23:33.149 --> 23:34.648
Do you want to mention the twins?

23:34.684 --> 23:36.283
[man] Double trouble.

23:36.319 --> 23:40.921
If Kyle and Lyle pick
you, be forewarned... boys?

23:40.957 --> 23:43.257
[together] We do everything together.

23:43.292 --> 23:44.636
- [women all gasp]
- [Nancy] So you are allowed

23:44.660 --> 23:47.328
to bow out if that's
not your cup of tea.

23:47.363 --> 23:49.897
Holy shit. It's a
fucking key party with coats.

23:49.932 --> 23:51.765
Holy shit.

23:51.801 --> 23:52.900
What does that mean?

23:52.935 --> 23:54.301
It means, Lester, dear,

23:54.337 --> 23:55.814
your night is about to get much better.

23:55.838 --> 23:57.082
[Nancy] Everyone makes his or her way

23:57.106 --> 23:58.839
back home by 6:00?

23:58.874 --> 24:01.475
Now, Art, host's choice:

24:01.510 --> 24:03.444
you want to go first, or
you want to pick last?

24:03.479 --> 24:04.957
- I want to pick first.
- [man] That a boy.

24:04.981 --> 24:07.781
Guy, can I get a
little drumroll, please?

24:07.817 --> 24:10.084
[suspenseful piano music]

24:10.119 --> 24:11.485
[laughter and light applause]

24:11.520 --> 24:14.288
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:14.323 --> 24:15.956
[dramatic piano flourish]

24:15.992 --> 24:18.359
- [applause and laughter]
- [woman] Whose is it?

24:18.394 --> 24:20.294
Who does this belong to?

24:20.329 --> 24:21.695
Whose is this?

24:21.731 --> 24:23.197
- [indistinct chatter]
- [woman] No.

24:23.232 --> 24:25.599
Come on. Don't be shy.

24:25.635 --> 24:28.469
- Anyone?
- [woman] Not mine.

24:28.504 --> 24:30.371
- [man] All right.
- [excited chatter]

24:30.406 --> 24:32.273
[woman] Yeah, there she is.

24:32.341 --> 24:34.041
[laughing]

24:34.076 --> 24:36.677
Looks like someone's anxious
to get this show on the road.

24:36.712 --> 24:39.680
- [all laugh]
- [man] Let the games begin.

24:39.715 --> 24:41.882
Enjoy him.

24:41.917 --> 24:44.051
It's here somewhere.

24:44.086 --> 24:45.452
Are you sure it's on this block?

24:45.488 --> 24:47.688
I parked it near a tree.

24:47.723 --> 24:49.456
Wait.

24:49.492 --> 24:51.959
Is that... that's it.

24:51.994 --> 24:53.994
I found it.

24:54.030 --> 24:56.897
Okay. You're not
driving. Give me the keys.

24:56.932 --> 24:59.199
You don't even have a license.

24:59.235 --> 25:00.668
Well, look.

25:00.703 --> 25:04.538
I think the options
are I risk going to jail

25:04.573 --> 25:07.274
or you risk ending up in a ditch.

25:10.780 --> 25:13.547
How long do you think they'd
put you away for?

25:18.120 --> 25:19.553
Bram, was it?

25:19.588 --> 25:21.255
You'll have to forgive my tan lines.

25:21.290 --> 25:22.656
No one on the ship warned us

25:22.692 --> 25:25.192
how strong the sun is on the equator.

25:25.227 --> 25:27.227
[indistinct chatter]

25:27.263 --> 25:28.729
- Uh...
- [exclaims and applause]

25:28.764 --> 25:31.532
Anyone? Anyone?

25:31.567 --> 25:33.067
[man] Come on. Don't be shy.

25:33.102 --> 25:36.036
"Expressly for you by
Miss Davenport," size six.

25:36.072 --> 25:37.771
[man] Honey, isn't that yours?

25:37.807 --> 25:39.551
- [woman] It's somebody's.
- [woman] Who is it?

25:39.575 --> 25:41.241
Pass.

25:41.277 --> 25:43.043
[man] There's no passing allowed, Adele.

25:43.079 --> 25:45.512
[woman] Come on, Adele.
You've done this before.

25:45.548 --> 25:47.548
Don't be a party pooper.

25:47.583 --> 25:49.516
Uh, it...

25:49.552 --> 25:50.584
It's... it's okay.

25:50.619 --> 25:52.386
She... she can pass.

25:52.421 --> 25:53.921
[whispers] Thank you.

25:53.956 --> 25:57.324
[people murmuring indistinctly]

26:09.805 --> 26:11.438
- [indistinct chatter]
- Good one, Randy.

26:11.474 --> 26:12.740
- [man] Yeah.
- [woman] Yeah.

26:12.775 --> 26:13.774
[man] Yeah.

26:13.809 --> 26:15.075
Look alive, maestro.

26:15.111 --> 26:17.444
Take the coat and don't ask questions.

26:17.480 --> 26:19.780
Oh, I'm not here to participate

26:19.815 --> 26:21.815
in whatever this is.

26:21.851 --> 26:23.550
[guests cheering]

26:23.586 --> 26:25.486
[laughter and applause]

26:25.521 --> 26:27.454
I was just hired to
play the piano till 9:00.

26:27.490 --> 26:28.834
I don't mean to burst your bubble,

26:28.858 --> 26:30.302
but I'm not trying to
get into your pants.

26:30.326 --> 26:32.166
Look, if it were up to
me, I'd be out the door,

26:32.194 --> 26:34.094
but my ride has
apparently up and disappeared

26:34.130 --> 26:36.397
right at the moment that everyone
has lost their mind

26:36.432 --> 26:38.999
and decided to start
playing sexual roulette.

26:39.034 --> 26:40.567
[cheers and applause]

26:40.603 --> 26:42.903
I'm not sure what
you're looking for from me.

26:42.938 --> 26:44.671
I'm looking for a little moral support

26:44.707 --> 26:46.306
from the only other homo at this party.

26:46.342 --> 26:49.309
Now take my goddamn coat.

26:49.345 --> 26:52.312
Thank you so much.

26:52.348 --> 26:55.115
How did you know that I was...

26:55.151 --> 26:57.418
You've played "Don't Rain on My Parade"

26:57.453 --> 26:59.486
twice in the last half hour.

26:59.522 --> 27:02.189
You might as well be wearing
a flashing sign.

27:02.224 --> 27:03.824
[woman] Moment of truth.

27:03.859 --> 27:05.292
[cheers and applause]

27:05.327 --> 27:06.927
[gasps] Oh, my God!

27:06.962 --> 27:08.162
[applause]

27:08.197 --> 27:09.329
[screams] Okay.

27:22.178 --> 27:25.379
What happened to my keys?

27:25.414 --> 27:27.848
Did you actually think that
this was going to happen?

27:27.883 --> 27:29.817
Oh, come on. I saw you in that bar

27:29.852 --> 27:31.163
