40:54.738 --> 40:57.206
Yeah, well, it saved my life.

40:57.241 --> 41:00.742
You never saw the person
that I was with those men.

41:00.778 --> 41:04.480
I am actually a carnal woman, Bill.

41:04.515 --> 41:06.648
I want a man to tear my clothes off,

41:06.684 --> 41:08.183
and I want to have sex in the shower,

41:08.219 --> 41:10.819
and if I am gonna go to a
five-hour charity dinner,

41:10.855 --> 41:14.089
at some point, I want to be felt
up under the goddamn table.

41:15.693 --> 41:17.359
I would've happily felt you up.

41:17.394 --> 41:18.594
Really?

41:18.629 --> 41:20.362
Yes.

41:20.397 --> 41:22.798
Those were some
incredibly boring dinners.

41:29.039 --> 41:32.040
The only thing that I ever
saw you be truly passionate about

41:32.076 --> 41:33.709
was your work.

41:37.081 --> 41:38.714
I didn't demand your passion.

41:38.749 --> 41:42.551
I just wanted you home for dinner.

41:44.054 --> 41:46.321
Stability above all else.

41:48.592 --> 41:50.459
It's pretty tragic, huh?

41:50.494 --> 41:52.127
No, don't say that.

41:55.766 --> 41:57.432
- It's true.
- It...

41:58.435 --> 42:00.002
It's not tragic.

42:02.006 --> 42:03.939
We did our best.

42:05.309 --> 42:07.409
We made three children.

42:10.848 --> 42:13.482
And I loved you, Libby.

42:13.517 --> 42:16.118
Maybe not the right way,

42:16.153 --> 42:18.020
maybe... maybe not enough.

42:20.691 --> 42:23.659
But I know that I loved you.

42:25.696 --> 42:28.063
I loved you too.

42:28.098 --> 42:31.066
<i>[melancholy piano music]</i>

42:31.101 --> 42:36.104
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:39.543 --> 42:42.544
[laughing]

42:48.185 --> 42:52.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:10.040 --> 43:13.041
[creaking, heavy breathing]

43:18.716 --> 43:20.649
- Are you close?
- Yeah. Yeah.

43:20.684 --> 43:22.150
Is there anything you want me to do?

43:22.186 --> 43:24.019
Say something sexy.

43:24.054 --> 43:26.188
Um...

43:26.223 --> 43:28.123
civil disobedience.

43:28.158 --> 43:29.825
[cries out]

43:32.429 --> 43:35.430
[both breathing heavily]

43:39.103 --> 43:40.836
It's quiet.

43:40.871 --> 43:42.971
Mm. That's the suburbs for you.

43:43.007 --> 43:46.375
No, I mean...

43:46.410 --> 43:49.211
you think they're
finished for the night?

43:49.246 --> 43:52.514
Because if so, my job here is done.

43:54.385 --> 43:58.220
Nancy gets stuffed up when she sleeps.

43:58.255 --> 44:02.891
Sometimes she has this little...

44:02.926 --> 44:04.192
nose whistle.

44:08.365 --> 44:12.434
Doesn't a part of you
think that if she truly loved you

44:12.469 --> 44:15.203
that you'd be enough for her?

44:15.239 --> 44:18.507
I know what I signed
up for. We made a deal.

44:18.542 --> 44:20.242
Well, deals get renegotiated.

44:20.277 --> 44:22.511
It'd be one thing if
you were okay with it,

44:22.546 --> 44:23.945
which happens to be my situation,

44:23.981 --> 44:25.247
but clearly, you're not.

44:25.282 --> 44:26.882
You tell me, Virginia,

44:26.917 --> 44:31.520
when is it ever absolutely
equal between partners anyway?

44:31.555 --> 44:33.422
Huh?

44:33.457 --> 44:36.258
Where you both feel exactly
the same thing for each other

44:36.293 --> 44:38.694
at the same time, in the same amount?

44:38.729 --> 44:40.429
If I want to,

44:40.464 --> 44:43.699
why can't I love her more
than she loves me?

44:43.734 --> 44:46.768
No man's ever loved you
more than you've loved him?

44:46.804 --> 44:47.869
What?

44:47.938 --> 44:49.905
Only all of them.

44:49.940 --> 44:52.607
It sounds like I'm bragging.

44:52.643 --> 44:55.610
I'm not. I'm really not.

44:55.646 --> 44:57.946
It's sad, actually.

45:00.350 --> 45:04.453
But has it ever occurred to
you, with all due respect,

45:04.488 --> 45:07.456
that maybe your wife is not...

45:07.491 --> 45:09.958
all that?

45:09.993 --> 45:13.595
Maybe it's you that she's
pretending with?

45:13.630 --> 45:16.264
You think you know her, but
you don't. Not really.

45:16.300 --> 45:18.633
If you really did know
her, her true self,

45:18.669 --> 45:20.335
then maybe she wouldn't be so...

45:20.370 --> 45:22.404
Dazzling?

45:22.439 --> 45:24.506
I don't care. It doesn't matter.

45:24.541 --> 45:26.074
How can it not matter?

45:26.110 --> 45:27.909
Your husband loves you, right?

45:27.945 --> 45:29.745
And what makes you worthy of his love?

45:29.780 --> 45:31.947
Is it because your respective
infidelities

45:31.982 --> 45:33.815
cancel each other out?

45:33.851 --> 45:37.919
Maybe he knows who you really are...

45:37.955 --> 45:40.622
not your body in bed
or your mind at work,

45:40.657 --> 45:42.958
but the secret you,

45:42.993 --> 45:44.926
the person you don't want anyone to see,

45:44.962 --> 45:47.195
much less acknowledge yourself,

45:47.231 --> 45:50.532
a woman who is fucked up,

45:50.567 --> 45:52.200
and he loves you anyway.

45:53.570 --> 45:56.505
Isn't that true love?

45:56.540 --> 45:58.206
Someone who'll kiss your bruises

45:58.242 --> 45:59.808
the same way he kisses your lips,

45:59.843 --> 46:02.477
who's on your side, not when it's easy,

46:02.513 --> 46:04.312
but when it's damn near impossible,

46:04.348 --> 46:06.882
when you yourself don't
think you deserve it?

46:17.761 --> 46:21.129
I have never been
hungrier in my entire life.

46:21.165 --> 46:23.398
Why is that?

46:23.433 --> 46:24.833
Well, you worked up an appetite.

46:24.868 --> 46:26.701
Hmm.

46:28.238 --> 46:30.005
I should probably be getting home.

46:30.040 --> 46:31.573
You want me to drive you?

46:31.608 --> 46:34.242
I was thinking I might walk.

46:34.278 --> 46:36.178
Bill, it's got to be, like, three miles.

46:36.213 --> 46:40.081
It's nice this time. Streets are empty.

46:40.117 --> 46:42.584
It's a good time to do some thinking.

46:42.619 --> 46:45.187
About what?

46:45.222 --> 46:47.689
About what happened here tonight.

46:47.724 --> 46:50.892
Mm. Let's not make too much of it.

46:50.928 --> 46:53.762
Pickle?

46:53.797 --> 46:55.463
Let's not make too little.

46:59.703 --> 47:02.771
You know what I'd really like?

47:02.806 --> 47:06.875
I mean really, really like?

47:06.910 --> 47:09.044
Well, you haven't been too
shy about asking so far.

47:09.079 --> 47:11.413
[laughs]

47:11.448 --> 47:13.815
Can you take Baxter for a pee?

47:15.886 --> 47:18.787
[Baxter whining]

47:18.822 --> 47:21.756
You got me into bed at last.

47:21.792 --> 47:23.959
That was the plan all along. Admit it.

47:23.994 --> 47:27.762
Art, the world's only reluctant swinger,

47:27.798 --> 47:30.866
was just an act.

47:30.901 --> 47:32.901
I know your coat, Virginia.

47:34.438 --> 47:38.106
You wear it to the office every day.

47:38.141 --> 47:40.141
So you picked me on purpose.

47:40.177 --> 47:42.244
- That I did.
- Aha.

47:42.279 --> 47:45.113
Because you wanted to go to bed with me.

47:46.350 --> 47:49.885
Because I knew you wouldn't.

47:49.920 --> 47:52.454
You're my boss,

47:52.489 --> 47:55.757
and bosses shouldn't
sleep with their employees.

47:55.792 --> 47:58.393
Not ever.

47:58.428 --> 48:00.328
Isn't that right?

48:02.933 --> 48:06.334
It happens. Sometimes it happens.

48:09.473 --> 48:11.806
How does it happen?

48:11.842 --> 48:14.142
Perhaps you have some special insight.

48:14.177 --> 48:15.477
I don't.

48:15.512 --> 48:17.612
Gonna have to use your imagination.

48:17.648 --> 48:19.748
What if we imagined together?

48:19.783 --> 48:22.484
- Why would we do that?
- Mm.

48:22.519 --> 48:25.320
Role-playing can be an
effective technique.

48:25.355 --> 48:28.590
Come on. I'm a shrink.

48:28.625 --> 48:30.125
Humor me a little, would you?

48:32.029 --> 48:35.330
Do I keep you late after work one night?

48:35.365 --> 48:37.599
Tell you my wife doesn't understand me,

48:37.634 --> 48:41.102
that we're
essentially living like roommates?

48:41.138 --> 48:43.038
When you request a raise,

48:43.073 --> 48:46.708
do I ask for a
little something in return?

48:51.815 --> 48:54.282
No. It's not like that.

48:54.318 --> 48:56.851
Okay, then.

48:56.887 --> 49:00.722
What is it like? Do I proposition you?

49:02.993 --> 49:05.694
No. You're awkward...

49:05.729 --> 49:08.630
and nervous.

49:08.665 --> 49:10.231
You do not know what you're doing.

49:10.267 --> 49:11.800
You barely even make eye contact.

49:11.835 --> 49:13.201
And then you take pity on me?

49:13.236 --> 49:16.905
No. I wait...

49:16.940 --> 49:20.675
until I feel something.

49:20.711 --> 49:22.344
An attraction?

49:22.379 --> 49:24.412
Mm...

49:24.448 --> 49:25.914
a shared passion.

49:25.949 --> 49:28.483
Not for each other, not at first.

49:28.518 --> 49:30.485
For the work.

49:30.520 --> 49:32.420
But I'm still the boss.

49:32.456 --> 49:33.989
I call the shots.

49:34.024 --> 49:38.226
Maybe at first, but not for very long.

49:38.261 --> 49:42.263
No. You want me to be your equal.

49:43.900 --> 49:47.335
Have the same
opportunities, the same success.

49:47.371 --> 49:50.171
Maybe that's just a
ruse to keep it going.

49:50.207 --> 49:54.442
No. No. You believe in me.

49:57.714 --> 49:59.914
You think I'm smart.

50:02.219 --> 50:06.021
Maybe even smarter
than you in some things.

50:06.056 --> 50:08.890
And you trust me.

50:08.925 --> 50:10.658
You defer to me.

50:13.630 --> 50:17.432
You see past the person
that I... I pretend to be,

50:17.467 --> 50:19.234
that I present to the world...

50:19.269 --> 50:22.237
Confident, competent in all things...

50:22.272 --> 50:25.240
To the person I am.

50:29.312 --> 50:33.581
Afraid...

50:33.617 --> 50:35.617
that I'm average.

50:38.588 --> 50:42.157
The ugly parts don't scare you away.

50:42.192 --> 50:44.526
You have ugly parts?

50:46.129 --> 50:49.597
I push you away,

50:49.633 --> 50:52.133
fall in and out of bed with other men,

50:52.169 --> 50:56.204
and somehow you love me...

50:58.275 --> 51:02.944
...enough to let me
go find my own happiness,

51:02.979 --> 51:05.280
even if it doesn't include you.

51:06.850 --> 51:09.617
So I'm a saint.

51:10.954 --> 51:12.787
No.

51:12.823 --> 51:15.323
No. You're broken too.

51:17.360 --> 51:19.027
You're afraid and...

51:21.031 --> 51:22.864
...and insecure.

51:24.734 --> 51:29.437
But I know all the broken places.

51:29.473 --> 51:33.208
You've shown them to me.

51:33.243 --> 51:36.177
So we've kissed each other's bruises.

51:38.315 --> 51:39.814
We have.

51:50.160 --> 51:52.660
Maybe he's the guy for you, Virginia.

51:57.167 --> 52:00.135
<i>["One" by Harry Nilsson]</i>

52:00.170 --> 52:04.739
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:04.774 --> 52:08.143
<i>♪ One is the loneliest number ♪</i>

52:08.178 --> 52:11.045
<i>♪ That you'll ever do ♪</i>

52:11.081 --> 52:12.514
[Lester snoring]

52:12.549 --> 52:15.583
<i>♪ Two can be as bad as one ♪</i>

52:15.619 --> 52:20.588
<i>♪ It's the loneliest
number since the number one ♪</i>

52:20.624 --> 52:22.590
[phone ringing]

52:22.626 --> 52:25.693
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:25.729 --> 52:28.029
[ringing continues]

52:28.064 --> 52:31.666
<i>♪ No is the saddest experience ♪</i>

52:31.701 --> 52:35.203
<i>♪ You'll ever know ♪</i>

52:37.140 --> 52:38.706
Hello?

52:38.742 --> 52:40.241
Uh, you've reached

52:40.277 --> 52:43.711
the Reproductive
Biology Research Foundation.

52:45.081 --> 52:49.417
Mrs. Johnson? Uh...

52:49.452 --> 52:52.487
[grunts] Let me just take a message.

52:54.891 --> 52:56.624
Okay.

52:56.660 --> 52:58.459
She'll call you back in the morning.

52:58.495 --> 52:59.861
Thank you.

52:59.896 --> 53:03.731
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:03.767 --> 53:06.201
<i>♪ It's just no good anymore ♪</i>

53:06.236 --> 53:09.537
<i>♪ Since you went away... ♪</i>

53:09.573 --> 53:11.105
[woman] <i>Operator.</i>

53:11.141 --> 53:13.208
Hello, may I have the number

53:13.243 --> 53:15.910
for the Checker Cab Company, please?

53:15.946 --> 53:20.949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:20.984 --> 53:23.518
You had them all along?

53:26.156 --> 53:28.323
I'm sorry.

53:28.358 --> 53:30.391
Forgive me?

53:30.427 --> 53:33.928
<i>♪ One is the loneliest number ♪</i>

53:33.964 --> 53:36.931
<i>♪ That you'll ever know ♪</i>

53:36.967 --> 53:38.399
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:38.468 --> 53:42.170
<i>♪ One is the loneliest number ♪</i>

53:42.205 --> 53:46.507
<i>♪ One is the loneliest number ♪</i>

53:46.543 --> 53:49.978
I hope you're capable
of changing your ways.

53:50.013 --> 53:53.448
Otherwise, I really don't
think this arrangement is gonna last.

53:53.483 --> 53:55.016
[barks]

53:55.051 --> 53:57.352
[knocking at door]

53:57.387 --> 53:58.419
[barks]

53:58.455 --> 54:00.955
This is not a reprieve.

54:04.728 --> 54:06.127
Oh.

54:06.162 --> 54:10.465
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:10.500 --> 54:12.967
Libby left her coat.

54:13.003 --> 54:14.369
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:14.404 --> 54:16.471
I'll see that she gets it. Thank you.

54:16.506 --> 54:20.642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:20.677 --> 54:22.343
Okay, then.

54:22.379 --> 54:25.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:25.315 --> 54:27.048
Bill?

54:27.083 --> 54:29.951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:29.986 --> 54:33.688
Bill, there's something
that I need to tell you.

54:33.723 --> 54:36.524
Dan and I aren't married.

54:36.559 --> 54:38.126
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:38.161 --> 54:41.696
We never got married.

54:41.731 --> 54:44.832
The reasons are complicated.

54:44.868 --> 54:48.569
And I know that I
should've told you this sooner,

54:48.605 --> 54:51.005
but it was just never the right time,

54:51.041 --> 54:53.207
and then it... it got away from me.

54:53.243 --> 54:54.375
I know.

54:54.411 --> 54:56.577
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:56.613 --> 54:57.945
You know?

54:57.981 --> 55:00.148
Yeah, I've known for a while.

55:00.183 --> 55:03.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:03.219 --> 55:06.254
I'm... I'm really sorry.

55:06.289 --> 55:07.989
What are you sorry for?

55:08.024 --> 55:10.992
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:11.027 --> 55:13.928
I'll see you at the office, Virginia.

55:13.963 --> 55:15.196
Drive safely.

